Hey there! To automate selecting all checkboxes on a page and then clicking a "Save" button in JavaScript, you can do something like this:

1. First, grab all the checkboxes using `document.querySelectorAll`.
2. Loop through those checkboxes and check each one.
3. Finally, find the "Save" button and click it.

Here's a quick example:

```javascript
// Step 1: Select all checkboxes
const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

// Step 2: Loop through and check them
checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
    checkbox.checked = true; // This checks each checkbox
});

// Step 3: Find the save button and click it
// Assuming your save button has an id of "saveButton"
document.getElementById('saveButton').click();
```

If your "Save" button doesn't have an ID, you can use other methods to select it, like by class name or even by its position in the DOM. For example:

```javascript
// Selecting by class name
document.querySelector('.save-button-class').click();

// Or by nth-child
document.querySelector('#formId input[type="submit"]:nth-child(2)').click();
```

Just make sure to adjust the selector to match your actual HTML structure. This should do the trick for automating the selection of all checkboxes and saving them!

